title: For Sale:  LWRC M6-SL
postcontent:
The new M6-SL is a replacement of our base model M6 rifle of old. The SL, which stands for 'stretch-lightweight', incoroprates everything a shooter needs in a quality light-weight base model rifle. Price and weight were the most important factors when developing the SL. With the M6-SL, LWRCI has brought to the market the lightest factory piston driven rifle to date.

The SL comes standard with Magpul furniture. A MOE mid-length handguard, MOE Stock, and MOE pistol grip provide excellent handling characteristics, while minimizing added weight. The SL utilizes the 'stretch' or mid-length piston system, providing a more direct recoil impulse for faster follow-up shots.

The most distinct feature of the SL is the barrel. The barrel still utilizes LWRCI's NiCorr surface conversion technology on a cold-hammer-forged barrel, but the barrel is of a smaller diameter to reduce weight.

The SL comes standard with the EXO (nickel-boron) plated one piece bolt carrier and the EXO coated enhanced fire control group. The SL also comes standard with a Daniel Defense A2 front sight post and a LWRC B.U.I.S. folding rear sight

The SL is a great addition to the LWRCI family of rifles. It provides users with an extremely lightweight rifle that incorporates our patented short-stroke piston operating system, has all of the advanced coatings that make our rifles the best in the world, and does so at an entry level price.

title: For Sale:  Polish Underfolder AK47
location: St. Pete/Pinellas Park, Tampa/St. Pete, Florida
postcontent:
1980 Polish Underfolder kit built on a US-made No Dak Spud NDS-1P receiver. This has the original factory chrome-lined barrel chambered in the original 7.62x39mm cartridge. I don't know who built it, but the rivets look great and everything is nice and straight. The rifle has a painted finish, like what you see on the new Bulgarian Arsenals. There are some nicks and scratches here and there, but nothing egregious. Polish underfolders have a much more straight stock compared to some of the other countries where the stock slopes downward. The straighter stock is better for using optics and places the recoil impulse more inline with the bore.

he AK47 market is crazy right now; here's a sweet deal just waiting to happen. Lots of people piece together "Tactical" AKs using the cheapest stuff they can find. There's none of that here! Kickass rifle, but I need to sell it to help fund another purchase. If you planned on a "tactical" AK47, this might be the one for you!

-TWS Dogleg railed receiver cover with peep sight. Made in the USA, the Dogleg uses a 3-point tension system that makes optics return-to-zero after opening and closing the cover. I have done several return-to-zero tests with this rail and it works just as advertised.

-Primary Arms MD-06L mini red dot optic. This red dot is a clone of the Aimpoint T1. The dot is 4MOA and the sight works nicely with the Dogleg rail. This model has the control knob on the left side. Some pretty impressive torture tests have been done on these little inexpensive optics.

-Mission First Tactical Engage Grip. Made in the USA, this grip has interchangeable front and back panels. It's sorta like the Magpul MIAD, but for AKs. All extra panels will be included.

-Damage Industries MKIII railed forend. Made in the USA, this rail locks up nice and tight and it looks great. The bottom rail is flush wth the receiver, which allows the underfolder stock to close and lock correctly. It comes with two picatinny rail sections (one has a QD hole) that can be placed at various locations along the rail. Perfect for mounting a light and/or a vertical grip, or an optic and/or laser if you prefer.

-Manticore Arms NightBrake. This is more of a brake than a flash hider. Made in the USA. It works well to tame the muzzle rise and it helps lessen recoil. Everything offered by Manticore is really well made. This brake is no exception.

-Tapco G2 Trigger. Without a doubt, the best product that this company makes! Trigger is nice and smooth. Counts as 3 US parts.

-Original handguards and pistol grip are included (as pictured)

title: For Sale:  ZM weapon LR300 upper reviver. Just selling the UPPER. It fits on any AR15 lower.  direct impingement upper reviv less than 200 rounds down the pipe. Comes with folding shoulder stock. 600.00obo 800.00 with EoTec
postcontent:
JUST SELLING THE UPPER. ALL U NEED IS A LOWER RECEIVER.  The upper is a LR 300 is an American assault rifle and conversion kit designed and manufactured by Z-M Weapons. It is based on the AR-15 platform and is broadly similar to the United States service rifle, the M16.

The weapon is touted as an exsuitability for military use in close quarters battle which often involves aggressive and rapid building entries requiring a compact yet powerful selective fire weapon.

Also notable is the rifle's capability to use a fully folding and adjustable skeletal stock. Most AR-15/M16 rifle variants have a thick, cylindrical recoil buffer tube, more properly called the receiver extension, that protrudes approximately 20 cm straight back from the rear of the receiver, and the firearm cannot operate without it. This normally precludes the use of anything but fixed or telescoping stocks. The LR 300 however uses an adapted version of the AR-15's standard direct impingement gas operating system which removes the need for a receiver extension and allows a folding stock.  The whole recoil system is in the mid length hang Guard witch really balances out the rifle and shoots like a dream with the stock folded in. 

Brand new these are well over 2000.00  will take 600.00obo 800.00 with EoTec
